Positive and Negative
Write a program to check whether the given number as input is positive, negative, or zero.

Sample 1:
Input
Output
20  
Positive  
Sample 2:
Input
Output
0
Zero
Sample 3:
Input
Output
-95
Negative
CODE:
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int n;
    // Reading the input number
    cin >> n;

    if (n > 0) {
        cout << "Positive" << endl;
    } else if (n < 0) {
        cout << "Negative" << endl;
    } else {
        cout << "Zero" << endl;
    }

    return 0;
}
